HEADWORD: kinaesthesis
<hw>kin`aes*the"sis</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>kinei^n</grk> to
move + <?/ perception.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The perception
attendant upon the movements of the muscles; the sensation accompanying
movement of the muscles.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>kin`es*the"sia</asp> and <asp>kin`es*the"sis</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Bastian.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
